206 = {
	name = "Robert" #Robert II le Pieux
	dynasty_house = house_capet
	dna = 206_robert_ii_capet
	religion = "catholic"
	culture = french
	martial = 6        # Increased from default - he was described as "a good soldier" though with mixed success
	diplomacy = 8      # Increased - he was described as "polished" and "amiable" 
	intrigue = 5       # Moderate - politically active but faced many conflicts
	stewardship = 7    # Good - managed territorial expansion and religious donations effectively
	learning = 9       # Increased significantly - he was highly educated, composed hymns, passionate about theology
	trait = education_learning_2
	trait = zealous    # Keeping - perfect for his deep religious devotion
	trait = stubborn   # His refusal to abandon marriage to Bertha despite excommunication and papal pressure
	trait = patient    # His 13-year persistent pursuit of Burgundy (1003-1016)
	trait = generous   # His constant charitable donations and aid to the poor mentioned in sources
	trait = scholar    # His intellectual pursuits, theology studies, hymn composition, and scholarly nature
	father = 200 #Hugues Capet
	mother = 233 #Adélaïde d'Aquitaine
	972.1.1 = {
		birth = "972.1.1"
		effect = {
			add_character_flag = has_scripted_appearance
		}
	}
	988.1.1 = {
		add_spouse = 1111 #Suzanne d'Italie (born Rozala d'Italie)
	}
	992.1.1 = {
		remove_spouse = 1111 #Suzanne d'Italie
	}
	996.10.1 = {
		add_spouse = 1147 #Berthe de Bourgogne
		give_nickname = nick_the_pious
		add_trait = excommunicated  # He was excommunicated for this marriage within prohibited degrees
	}
	1003.1.1 = { #circa
		remove_spouse = 1147 #Berthe de Bourgogne
		remove_trait = excommunicated  # Excommunication lifted after annulment
	}
	1003.1.5 = { #circa
		add_spouse = 333 #Constance d'Arles
	}
	1031.1.1 = {
		trait = ill
	}
